item.title: First Model: Lightsaber :)
item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

[quote=“sirwayne, post:19, topic:334153”][quote author=rip4d link=topic=430539.msg3170672#msg3170672 date=1270417949]
I can safely say that no lightsabers have a spike at the very bottom of the handle without ever once watching the series.
[/quote]
The games though. Darth Vaders apprentice had spikes on the end of his saber hilt. Many Star Wars games have spikes on the bottoms of the hilt.[quote author=Javafire link=topic=430539.msg3170746#msg3170746 date=1270422743]
focus on the blade and less with the handle, now if you could make it turn on and off with a few lines of code that would be awesome i’ve done that before so it is possible.
[/quote]
Thats a good idea. One thing though, a blade is pretty simple to model. I cant see how I can focus more on it. There was more to the blade but I deleted because I accidently changed the colour. It looked strange lol[/quote]

Why don’t you just try a whole new model. This was your first, why don’t you move onto something bigger?
